text: Muhammad Pasha of Rawanduz (Kurdish: Mîr Mihemed Paşa, ; also known as Mirê Kor, Kor Mir- the "blind prince"; born in Rawandiz; 1783–1838) was the Kurdish Mir of the Soran Emirate (1813–1838). He sent his troops against Nisibin and Mardin farther north, seized Cizre. == References ==
title: Muhammed Pasha Of Rawandiz
